# Restaurant POS SaaS Project Rules

## API Design Principles
- Follow OpenAPI 3.1 specification exactly as defined in openapi.yaml
- Use consistent REST patterns: GET for retrieval, POST for creation, PUT for updates, DELETE for removal
- Implement proper HTTP status codes: 200 for success, 201 for creation, 400 for validation errors, 401 for auth errors, 403 for forbidden, 404 for not found
- Use consistent JSON response format with proper error handling
- Apply rate limiting for SaaS usage quotas per client
- Implement proper pagination using limit parameter (default 20, max 100)

## Authentication and Authorization
- Implement dual authentication: X-API-KEY header for client identification and Bearer JWT for user auth
- Use different security levels: ApiKeyAuth for basic operations, BearerAuth for sensitive operations
- Track and enforce monthly usage limits per API key
- Implement proper JWT token validation and expiration handling
- Use Spring Security method-level security where appropriate

## Database and Entity Design
- Create JPA entities for: Item, Order, OrderItem, Employee, Payment, Printer, PrintTemplate, PrintJob
- Use UUIDs for entity IDs for better scalability
- Implement proper entity relationships with lazy loading
- Use database indexes for frequently queried fields
- Apply soft delete pattern where data retention is required
- Use database constraints for data integrity

## Print Management System
- Design flexible printer registration system with category-based organization
- Implement template engine for print formatting (consider using Thymeleaf or Freemarker)
- Create print job queue with status tracking (pending, printing, completed, failed)
- Support multiple printer categories: oven, grill, cashier, customer_copy, etc.
- Implement asynchronous print job processing using Virtual Threads
- Create audit trail for all print operations

## Business Logic Patterns
- Calculate order totals from item prices and quantities
- Generate unique order numbers for customer tracking
- Implement proper order status lifecycle: pending → completed/canceled
- Handle payment methods: cash, card, tap with proper validation
- Create customer receipt copies with order tracking information
- Implement employee role-based access control

## Testing and Quality Assurance
- Write unit tests for all service methods using JUnit 5 and Mockito
- Create integration tests for API endpoints using @SpringBootTest
- Test authentication and authorization scenarios
- Mock external dependencies in tests
- Achieve minimum 80% code coverage
- Use TestContainers for database integration tests

## Error Handling and Logging
- Create custom exceptions for business validation errors
- Implement global exception handler with proper error responses
- Use structured logging with correlation IDs for request tracing
- Log all authentication attempts and usage quota checks
- Monitor print job failures and implement retry mechanisms
- Create health checks for database and external dependencies

## Performance and Scalability
- Use Virtual Threads for IO-intensive operations like database queries and print job processing
- Implement connection pooling for database connections
- Use caching strategically for frequently accessed data like menu items
- Optimize database queries with proper indexing
- Design for horizontal scaling with stateless services
- Monitor API response times and database query performance
